<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1398843-i-ve-seen-a-lot-of-people-mark-this-as">I&#39;ve seen a lot of people mark this as historical fiction. I&#39;m only a couple of chapters in, but it feels like it&#39;s set in modern day. Am I missing something?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1398843'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F11469379-a-walk-across-the-sun">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1398843-i-ve-seen-a-lot-of-people-mark-this-as">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1398843-i-ve-seen-a-lot-of-people-mark-this-as">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/83051753-joan"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/83051753-joan">Joan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would say it is a fairly recent modern day book. A lot of it takes place in Mumbai (formerly Bombay). It is definitely not Historical Fiction. It is<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would say it is a fairly recent modern day book. A lot of it takes place in Mumbai (formerly Bombay). It is definitely not Historical Fiction. It is about today's sex trade-- more of an expose novel. The book I read had a recommendation by John Grisham on the cover and the book reminded me of Grisham's style of writing exposes.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
